Automation team is currently working on improving the framework by replacing the hardcoded test data with dynamically generated data. As static data can become unreliable between the executions, the focus now is on ensuring that valid up-to-date data is available for every test run. To achieve this, a DB Utility component has been implemented to execute SQL queries dynamically, and integrate it into test scripts, removing the need for static data. So we need support from development/database team to get those queries.

Below are the requirements for Test Data:

Transfers:

Agent- Login IDs and the Herd Ids under the agent with available entitlements

Individual- Login IDs and the Herds Ids with available entitlements

ETF- Login IDs and the Herds Ids associated with the ETF with available entitlements

NR-CISYF

Agent Logins with the Herd IDs that have not yet started or initiated the application process.

Agent Logins with the Herd IDs where the application has been initiated/ is in editable mode.

Agent Logins with the Herd IDs  that have successfully submitted the application.
